Did You Lose Money With BP Prudhoe Bay Royalty Trust (BPT)?

Andrew Stoltmann /
BPT, fraud, investment fraud, lawsuit, oil and gas scams, prudhoe bay royalty trust / 

Did your broker or brokerage firm recommend that you invest in BP Prudhoe Bay Royalty Trust (BPT)? If so, the attorneys at Stoltmann Law Offices are interested in speaking with you about those losses. BPT holds non-operational interests in minerals in the Prudhoe Bay oil field located on the North Slope of Alaska. It is based in Houston, Texas. BPT pays out royalties based on production in the North Slope, but revenues have fallen for the past two years. Oil, gas and energy investments, which BPT is one of them, tend to be risky and highly illiquid investments that are not suitable for all investors. If you were sold BPT investments, we may be able to help you bring a securities arbitration claim against the brokerage firm for not reasonably supervising its employees and allowing them to recommend unsuitable investments. Please call today at 312-332-4200. The call is free with no obligation.











