Did your Hilliard Lyons broker recommend Breitburn Energy investments? If so, the attorneys at Stoltmann Law Offices are interested in speaking with you about those investments. Breitburn Energy Partners is an oil and gas and energy investment, and many of these can be highly illiquid and risky ones, not suitable for many investors. Breitburn has since filed for bankruptcy, causing many investors to lose their investment money. A Hilliard Lyons broker has an ironclad obligation to only recommend and sell those investments that are suitable for the customer. If he does not, Hilliard Lyons may be responsible for the customer’s losses. Please call our securities law firm today at 312-332-4200 for a free consultation about your losses with Hillard Lyons. We take cases on a contingency fee basis only.











March 9, 2017 /
