Andrew Stoltmann /
Energy Hunter Partners, fraud, investment fraud, lawsuit, magnum hunter resources corp / 

Did you lose money with Energy Hunter Partners? If so, the attorneys at Stoltmann Law Offices are interested in speaking with you about your losses. We may be able to file an arbitration claim in the Financial Industry Regulatory Authority (FINRA) on your behalf against the brokerage firm that sold you this unsuitable investment. Magnum Hunter Resources Corp is an independent oil and gas company engaged in the exploration of crude oil, natural gas and liquids in the U.S. and Canada. It is based in Irving, Texas. Magnum Hunter filed for bankruptcy in December 2015 and Energy Hunter Partners 2011 has been dissolved. Products such as investments in oil, gas and energy involve a high degree of risk and are typically sold as unregistered securities. A broker must take into account an investor’s age, investment objectives and net worth before recommending a product. If he does not, and the product is unsuitable, the brokerage firm may be liable for losses. If you suffered losses because of your brokerage firm, please call our law offices today at 312-332-4200.










